videoSnippet.title: The Grim Reaper! || Carlsen vs Keymer || FIDE World Rapid Championship (2022)
videoSnippet.description:
Photos by Lenart Ootes
Have a great day :)

Carlsen, Magnus (2834) - Keymer, Vincent (2590)
FIDE World Rapid Championship (chess24.com) [10] 2022.12.28
E04 Catalan, open, 5.Nf3

1.c4 Nf6 2.d4 e6 3.Nf3 d5 4.g3 dxc4 5.Bg2 c6 6.Ne5 Bb4+ 7.Bd2 Be7 8.Bg5 h6 9.Bxf6 Bxf6 10.Na3 Qa5+ 11.Qd2 Qxd2+ 12.Kxd2 O-O 13.Naxc4 Rd8 14.Ke3 Nd7 15.Rhd1 Nb6 16.f4 Be7 17.Rac1 f6 18.Nd3 Kf7 19.Na5 Rb8 20.Bf3 Bd6 21.Kf2 Nd5 22.a3 Bc7 23.b4 Bxa5 24.bxa5 Bd7 25.e4 Nc7 26.Ke3 Be8 27.Nb4 Ke7 28.e5 Nd5+ 29.Bxd5 cxd5 30.Rc7+ Rd7 31.Rdc1 fxe5 32.dxe5 Kd8 33.R7c5 d4+ 34.Kd2 Bg6 35.a6 Be4 36.Rb5 b6 37.Nc6+ Bxc6 38.Rxc6 Rc8 39.Rxe6 d3 40.Rd6 Rxd6 41.exd6 Kd7 42.Rf5 Ke6 43.d7 Rd8 44.Re5+ Kd6 45.Re3 Kc6 46.Rxd3 Kb5 47.Ke3 Kxa6 48.Ke4 Kb7

12:20 Pause the Video!
13:30 It was In This Position!
15:10 Contributions!

The FIDE Women's World Rapid Championship is an 11-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $150,000, with a $40,000 top prize.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com
